From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Crelia <crelia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] NeoForge Structure Settings Getter

Adds getModifiedStructureSettings() method to
net.minecraft.world.level.levelgen.structure.Structure. This is a simple
getter wrapper that the NeoForge coremod ReplaceFieldWithGetterAccess targets.

At runtime, NeoForge's real ModifiableStructureInfo replaces this getter.
For compile time, this returns the backing field directly.

diff --git a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/levelgen/structure/Structure.java b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/levelgen/structure/Structure.java
index 3fbd6e8d23f2e6020532530ef8ad7e64b8047d4b..bbbb0000bbbb0000bbbb0000bbbb0000bbbb00 100644
--- a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/levelgen/structure/Structure.java
+++ b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/levelgen/structure/Structure.java
@@ -54,6 +54,16 @@
     public HolderSet<Biome> biomes() {
         return this.settings.biomes;
     }
 
+    // NeoForge start - modifiable structure accessor (compile-time stub)
+    /**
+     * Returns the (possibly modified) structure settings.
+     * NeoForge's coremod replaces direct field access to settings with this method.
+     */
+    public StructureSettings getModifiedStructureSettings() {
+        return this.settings;
+    }
+    // NeoForge end
+
     public Map<MobCategory, StructureSpawnOverride> spawnOverrides() {
         return this.settings.spawnOverrides;
     }
